    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="180"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/4060: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 5, 1934—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. My despatch No. 1419, February 1.<note n="12" xml:id="d180fn12">Not
                        printed.</note> Rickard informs me he is leaving for Washington by air
                    tomorrow via Miami under instructions of the President to endeavor to expedite
                    negotiations with Foreign Bondholders Protective Council regarding Dominican
                    debt question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
